Package de.btu.openinfra.backend.db.daos Description

This package implements all DAO classes which are used to access the JPA persistence layer (database). All DAO classes should derive the abstract OpenInfraDao class which is used to provide a generalized method for instantiating these DAO objects. Furthermore, there exists a second abstract class OpenInfraValueDao which ads the functionality to retrieve a specific POJO object from database by a specified value. There are two exceptions of the aforementioned rule. The following classes do not implement the above-stated classes: TopicDao TopicInstanceParentDao Moreover, there is a distinction between 'ordinary' DAO classes and 'view' DAO classes. Ordinary DAO classes are used for both data access and data storage. View DAO classes are special view classes which must not be used for data storage TopicInstanceDao. In order to map locale objects of the form 'de-DE' which are used in the HTML view you should use the forLanguageTag method located in the class PtLocaleDao.
